  "question_id": "341b6b68-7df3-4a0c-9503-0857de1673a6",
  "short_text": "Print Required Characters",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a string and prints the **a** and **z** characters in the string.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing a string.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should contain all the **a** and **z** characters in the string, each on a new line.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given string is **zigzag**,\n\n- The characters in the string **zigzag** are **z**, **i**, **g**, **z**, **a** and **g**.\n- The **a** and **z** characters in the string are **zza**.\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\nz\nz\na\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "dcf06290-2e5c-4341-9a43-494692bdc87b",
      "code_content": "string = input()\n\nfor each_character in string:\n    if (each_character == \"a\") or (each_character == \"z\"):\n        print(each_character)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
